HEADWORD: Unruffled
<hw>Un*ruf"fled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>ruffled</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not ruffled or
agitated; smooth; calm; tranquil; quiet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Calm and <qex>unruffled</qex> as a summer's sea.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

